article.description: — Loren Cristian Jackson had 31 points as Akron edged past Kent State 66-62 on Friday night.
article.headline: Jackson scores 31 to lift Akron past Kent St. 66-62
article.linkText: Jackson scores 31 to lift Akron past Kent St. 66-62
article.story: AKRON, Ohio -- — Loren Cristian Jackson had 31 points as Akron edged past Kent State 66-62 on Friday night. Enrique Freeman had 10 points and nine rebounds for Akron (4-1, 2-0 Mid-American Conference), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Camron Reece added seven rebounds. Mike Nuga had 19 points and eight rebounds for the Golden Flashes (3-2, 0-1). Danny Pippen added 16 points and nine rebounds. Justyn Hamilton had four blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
